pan><hr size=1> I worked until my first was 17 months old, then I quit to stay home and have been here for 4 years now. It felt like the right thing to do for my family, and the financial sacrifice has been worth the peace of mind I get by caring for them myself.<br>
<br>
I love being home with my 2 kids, but am totally sympathetic to anyone who has to work. It bothers me when people denigrate working mothers because I know I loved my daughter every bit as much back when I had a full time job. There were times when I felt I &quot;had it all&quot; but many more times when I just felt overwhelmed and exhausted. My only regret about quitting was that I didn't do it the day she was born.<br>
<br>
I am so impressed by the way ALL of you ladies, atheist and Christian, SAHM and working, have been so respectful in your replies no matter which side you fall on. I don't think there should be a controversy, we are all doing the best we can for our children in a world that expects too much from women. <br>
<br>
DL<br>
