<br>
of course things have taken a bit of a turn, SO had to quit his job because of hostile working conditions and ive been working pretty close to full time for the last 3 weeks.  he is not having fun being the sahd and im not really enjoying being away from the kids so much.  its just not working for us in reverse kwim?  its going to be interesting to see how things start going this fall when i start school to get my opticians license (finally, ive only been doing the same work for half the pay for the last 7 yrs) its going to be really tricky finding a good balance without having to get some form of outside care for my kids, since i have problems with daycare and stuff (bad experiences as a child in daycare growing up, lets just say im biased), much less the fact that if i have to pay for daycare for 3 kids....wtf am i trying to work part time and further my education for!!!  but its something that i really need to do, in that 'this is for me' sort of way.<br>
<br>
okie, nuff babbling.  btw, the 2 1/2 yo whining for 12 hours thing...oh yeah, i hear ya totally!!!  oh and the religion thing, not a factor since im athiest, but the whole 'womens place is in the home' really burns me and my IL's church is real goofy about that so i get to hear about it all the time &quot;even though im working its good that we dont just throw our kids in daycare and forget about them&quot; so says FIL....well im just so glad he approves...<br>
<br>
michelle<br>
